data.title: Events
data.text:
Our Events

Paraguayan Socials

The Paraguayan Social was born as a collaborative idea between the PSA board and the Paraguayan students at k-state, with the sole purpose of promoting a friendly environment for students and faculty to learn, share, exchange cultural similarities, differences and, ideas, while being able to practice Spanish, have a bite of Paraguayan food (when available), learn about different topics from Paraguay and have fun! There's no need to be proficient in Spanish; the point is for all to meet and chat, away from the pressure of a classroom, just like you would with friends.
